target.value: 100% of meteostations gauging main meteo parameters 93% of stream gauges reporting operational data 87% stream gauges measuringdischarges

actual.value: 97% of meteostations gauging main meteo parameters.64% of stream gauges reporting operational data.74% stream gauges measuringdischarges.

title.narrative: (Comp C: Tajikistan, IRI 2) Better transmission of data to global telecommunication system (GTS)
Increased accuracy and timeliness of basic weather forecasts
(Comp B: Kyrgyz Republic, IRI 2) Better transmission of data to global telecommunication system (GTS)
(Comp B: Kyrgyz Republic, IRI 4) Increased institutional strength and sustainability of Kyrgyzhydromet

baseline.value: Existing legal structure, operating procedures and staffing are inadequate to meet KgHM mission#s needs.Investment and O&M needsfar exceed KgHM budgets.

target.value: New regulations developed.New standard operating procedures developed.New business plan developed.Budget significantlyincreased.

actual.value: Kyrgyzhydromet again changed its jurisdiction, leaving the structure of the Ministry of Natural Resources, Ecology and TechnicalSupervision and returning to the Ministry of Emergency Situations. The process of updating the legal framework of Kyrgyzstan isongoing.

title.narrative: (Comp C: Tajikistan, IRI 3) Increased sustainability and strengthened performance of Tajikhydromet operations

baseline.value: Existing legal structure, operating procedures and staffing are inadequate to meet TjHM mission needs.Investment and O&M needsfar exceed TjHM budgets.

target.value: New regulations developed.New standard operating procedures developed.New business plan developed.Budget significantlyincreased.

actual.value: To be completed in the next 2 months, advisory services for institutional strengthening and improvement of Tajikhydromet servicedelivery is developing new technical standard operating procedures and technical manuals. A development strategy and plan,including investment estimates for the short-term (2 years), medium-term (6 years) and long-term (10 years), is also beingfinalized.Tajikhydromet has moved into a new and modern building, the finalization of which was in part supported by theADB.

title.narrative: (Comp C: Tajikistan, IRI 5) Increased reliability of climate data

baseline.value: Information on climate limited and of inadequate quality

target.value: Ability to downscale to local scales for at least 90% of the country

actual.value: Ability to downscale local scales for at least 85% of the country

title.narrative: Increased accuracy of river flow forecasts
(Comp A: EC-IFAS, IRI 1): Improved access to national and regional numeric weather prediction products to all CA countries

target.value: 7x7 km every 6 hours for all of Central Asia2x2 km every 6 hours for the mountainous region of Central Asia

actual.value: The COSMO numerical weather prediction (NWP) model has faced service interruptions, likely due to interruptions from Roshydrometdelivering boundary conditions. Uzhydromet is therefore implementing a process chain for receiving initial conditions from theGerman Weather Service (DWD). After obtaining the full volume of the initial conditions, COSMO will start sequentially computing onthe 6.6 km and 2.2 km grids.

title.narrative: (Comp A: EC-IFAS, IRI 2): Established platform for integration of five NHMSs in CA

baseline.value: Lack of agreed regional approaches on knowledge exchange and emergency procedures

target.value: Regional approach adopted in hydromet forecasting and decision-making mechanism for regional issues formalized among the four NHMSsin CA

actual.value: Training modules for delivery through the CAHMP-established distance learning system with nodes in Kazakhstan, Kyrgyz Republic,Tajikistan and Uzbekistan are currently being determined. A regional meeting was held in October 2021 as part of the IFASintergovernmental sessions. The next regional CAHMP meeting will be organize in the last quarter of 2022.

title.narrative: Increased user satisfaction with hydrometeorological services
(Comp A: EC-IFAS, IRI 3): Improved access to landslide, mudflow and snowmelt guidance for all CA countries

baseline.value: CARFFGS provides only flash flood guidance products across the region

target.value: CARFFGS provides flash flood, landslide, riverine routing and snowmelt guidance products across the region

actual.value: Supply and installation of equipment (modernization of existing equipment with new servers) and software (landslide, snowmelt andriver routing routines) for CARFFGS was initiated in January 2022.
